		<tr>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				In the pre-realease FAQ Verant lied so much about stuff it was going too put in the game. They even said you could own a boat!!! <br>  <br> There were questions like this on the FAQ. <br>  <br> Q:Can I own a house? <br>  <br> A:Yes you could own a house but it would the cost a lot of money. <br>  <br> They even elaborated further on this: <br>  <br> Q:Can you have a house underground? <br>  <br> A: Yes we would have no problems with underground houses. <br>  <br> I've enver heard of even a level 50 owning a house! If you dont believe me go find a copy and read it yourself. <br> They also said guilds gould have uniforms and a guildhouse and stuff. <br> They said they would be hiring full time world builders to make new zones. The only new zones are The hole, temple of solusek ro and paineel. the map that came in he box had all this stuff on it like dragonscale hills. the unkempt woods. the hatchlands. the hills of shade. broken skull rock. wayunder lake. lake neriuss. the grand plateau and many others. NONE OF THESE PLACES EXIST!!! They said all this crap about Everquest being a ever expanding world shaped by the players and made the game sound more complicated and fun and big than it really is. A magazine review (pc gamer I think) said that the AI is incredible and a hill giant ran away at first and then circled around a hill and ambushed the person that was writing the article. A GM was probably controlling it just so the reviewer would write that. The extent of the AI is if something glares at you threatingly or scowls at you ready to attack when it sees you it chases you until you die or you kill it. <br> Find a copy of the pre-release FAQ and read it for yourself. These were just a few examples of stuff they lied about.		

