				I have been programming since age 8, and I know setting up such an environment as EQ is tough, but not nearly as hard as you all are making out. 3D engines are mainstream now, and in some cases Open Source (free). <br>  <br> EQ is technically out-of-date. For instance, the physics model they use is, well, rigged-- every seen sharks swimming above ships? Its cause anything that swims under a ship popps up above. If you tested EQ beta, you know of the fall-through-world bug. EQ has been hacked up so much by the developers trying to solve problems the fastset and easiest way, that much is inconsistant (bad programming style and planning). <br>  <br> The fact is that they did not plan for the problems to pop up, but it should not hinder development of new zones, reconstructing better AI, etc. That is what the Test server is for. It sounds to me like they had a change of management, or something.. I don't know. <br>  <br> Now, I also know a little about bussiness management and marketing. They are setting up for EQ2-- they did not expect 3D engines to be the MAIN concentration of almost every game developer out there, resulting in awesome 3D that is much better than EQ. Kunark, for instance, is revamped with a new engine-- thats why they said EQ would have to be rewritten from the ground up to make all the world behave as Kunark. Ever seen the Kunark boat? ITs HUGE-- if the normal EQ boats were any bigger than they are now, they crash left and right. <br>  <br> The point is, that they must rewrite EQ from the ground up. They expected that they could have all those features, but it turned out that they couldn't do it. Revamping the system costs money, and thats why we paid for Kunark and Kunark is technically superior to EQ in every way. The planes (hate, air, etc) were the first &quot;free expansion&quot; to EQ; see any better graphics or cooler, larger things? Nope, it uses the same engine version as EQ. <br>  <br> What all this means: If you want awesome graphics all over EQ, a good, solid environment, an expandable world, and all the goodies, you're going to have to wait until EQ2 or some sort of all-encompassing expansion. <br>  <br> One qualm I have is they are doing the same (stopped putting in new features) with some of the actual roll-playing stuff, such as the Enchanter's spell line of Thicken Mana (and Crystalize Mana). Only the Wu Gauntlets exist, and for an expance of enchanter's applications, this line of spells is JUST what is needed (up until now enchanters were jewelry makers, yet now they may take on any trade), but Verant screwed the plan to the wall. No plans for adding more items/armors/weapons =(. BAD move, Verant. Very bad.. many Enchanters are very pissed off, and frankly, I am too. There is no POSSIBLE reason why the spell line should not be expanded... Very irresponsible, Verant. Just my little rant...  <br>  <br> -Will		

